      ],
      "summary": "The Islamic Medical Association of North America (IMANA) is a professional and humanitarian organization that fosters health promotion and disease prevention through <cite id=\"1\">direct patient care and global health programs</cite>. Operating with a mission to provide medical relief to vulnerable populations, IMANA has established a significant international footprint, serving regions including <cite id=\"10\">Gaza, Jordan, Yemen, and Pakistan</cite>. The organization maintains <cite id=\"1\">an overall score of 99.99.75/100 from Charity Navigator</cite>, reflecting exceptional standards of accountability and transparency. Financially, IMANA reported <cite id=\"3\">total revenue of $2,874,345</cite> in its most recent filing, with a <cite id=\"3\">program expense ratio of 68.7%</cite>, indicating that nearly all of its functional expenses are dedicated to its core medical missions. Beyond emergency response, the organization supports <cite id=\"10\">Continuing Medical Education (CME) and medical grants</cite>, positioning itself as both a relief agency and a professional hub for Muslim healthcare providers. As a <cite id=\"2\">zakat-eligible charity</cite>, IMANA provides a verified channel for donors to fulfill religious obligations through healthcare initiatives that serve the <cite id=\"2\">poor (fuqara) and needy (masakin)</cite>.",
